threshold used

SECTION 7 — ROLE CLASSIFICATION
Derived from Asian Handicap.
Pick-em:
 |AH| ≤ 0.25
Narrow Favourite:
 -0.5
Moderate Favourite:
 -0.75 to -1.25
Strong Favourite:
 ≤ -1.5
Underdog:
 Opposite side of favourite.

SECTION 8 — BASE POINTS
Result scoring:
Win = 3
 Draw = 1
 Loss = 0
Adjusted by favourite burden:
Pick-em = 1.00
 Underdog = 1.00
 Narrow Favourite = 0.95
 Moderate Favourite = 0.90
 Strong Favourite = 0.85

SECTION 9 — MARKET ROLE ADJUSTMENT
Context reward / penalty.
Favourite examples:
home win = 0
home draw = -0.25
home loss = -0.50
away win = +0.50
Underdog examples:
away win = +0.60
away draw = +0.30
home win = +0.25
Pick-em = 0

SECTION 10 — HT/FT ADJUSTMENT
Use halftime-to-fulltime resilience table.
Examples:
HT lose → FT win = strong positive
HT win → FT loss = strong negative
HT draw → FT draw = neutral/slight negative

SECTION 11 — IGDEV SYSTEM
Core Formula:
IGDev = NonPenaltyGoals - ImpliedGoals
Source Rule:
Use authoritative file fields if present.
If absent, derive only from available market fields.
Important Rule:
If user says they provide performance flags manually:
Do not override with self-generated flags.

SECTION 12 — USER-PROVIDED PERFORMANCE FLAGS
